content:
To get the most out of the Group Voluntary Benefits Application, you need to understand how it's built. 

The product model underpins all the business processes used in the Group Voluntary Benefits line of business. It has the products:

Member Based: Medical, Vision, Dental, Critical Illness

Summary Based: Dental Summary

Here's the high-level product model for the Critical Illness root product:

Coverages

* The spec that models a coverage provided as part of an insurance or health product.
* To learn about the coverage specs for member-based products, see Coverages for Member-based Products.
* To learn about the coverage specs for summary-based products, see Coverages for Summary-Based Products

Rating Facts

* The spec that contains attributes used to rate an insurance or health product.
* Attributes in a rating fact spec are data needed to rate a product, but aren't stored with the product.

Attributes

* All the attributes used in the member-based and summary-based product models and coverage specs are defined in the Vlocity Attribute Designer.
* Attributes are arranged into Attribute Categories.

Group Voluntary Benefits Attribute Catalog
All attributes used for the Group Voluntary Benefits line of business are listed by Attribute Category.

Coverages for Member-based Products

* The spec that models a coverage provided as part of an insurance or health product.
* Defines the required and optional coverages on an insurance product.

Coverages for Summary-Based Products

* The spec that models a coverage provided as part of an insurance or health product.
* Defines the required and optional coverages on an insurance product.
title: Understanding Vlocity Insurance Product Models
